approve(address,uint256).details: Sets `account` as the approved account to manage token `id`. Requirements: - Token `id` must exist. - The caller must be the owner of the token,   or an approved operator for the token owner. Emits an {Approval} event.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the number of tokens owned by `owner`. Requirements: - `owner` must not be the zero address.

emergencyWithdraw(address).details: Only the owner can call this function.

params.token: The address of the token to withdraw.

getApproved(uint256).details: Returns the account approved to manage token `id`. Requirements: - Token `id` must exist.

returns._0: The current price per call asset.

params.premium: Premium being paid for the position

params.amount: The amount of the underlying asset.
params.isPut: Whether the option is a put or call.
params.lastPrice: The last price of the underlying asset.
params.strike: The strike price of the option.

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Returns whether `operator` is approved to manage the tokens of `owner`.

multicall(bytes[]).details: Receives and executes a batch of function calls on this contract.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

ownerOf(uint256).details: Returns the owner of token `id`. Requirements: - Token `id` must exist.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Transfers token `id` from `from` to `to`. Requirements: - Token `id` must exist. - `from` must be the owner of the token. - `to` cannot be the zero address. - The caller must be the owner of the token, or be approved to manage the token. - If `to` refers to a smart contract, it must implement   {IERC721Receiver-onERC721Received}, which is called upon a safe transfer. Emits a {Transfer} event.

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Sets whether `operator` is approved to manage the tokens of the caller. Emits an {ApprovalForAll} event.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See: https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165 This function call must use less than 30000 gas.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfers token `id` from `from` to `to`. Requirements: - Token `id` must exist. - `from` must be the owner of the token. - `to` cannot be the zero address. - The caller must be the owner of the token, or be approved to manage the token. Emits a {Transfer} event.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateAddress(address,address,address,ad.details: Only the owner can call this function.

params._dpFee: The address of the Dopex fee contract.
params._feeTo: The address of the fee recipient.
params._optionPricing: The address of the option pricing contract.
params._pool: The address of the UniswapV3 pool.
params._statusPools: Whether the UniswapV3 pool is enabled.
params._tokeURIFetcher: The address of the token URI fetcher.

params._delegateTo: The address of the new exercise delegate.
params._status: The status of the exercise delegate (true to enable, false to disable).

emergencyWithdraw(address).notice: Performs an emergency withdraw of all tokens from the contract.

getCurrentPricePerCallAsset(address).notice: Calculates the current price per call asset.

getFee(uint256,uint256).notice: Gets the fee for the option

getPremiumAmount(bool,uint256,uint256,ui.notice: Calculates the premium amount for the given option parameters.

getPricePerCallAssetViaTick(address,int2.notice: Calculates the price per call asset for the given tick.

mintOption(((address,address,address,int.notice: Mints an option for the given strike and expiry.

name().notice: Provides the name of the token

positionSplitter((uint256,address,uint25.notice: Splits the given option into a new option.

symbol().notice: Provides the symbol of the token

tokenURI(uint256).notice: Provides the tokenURI for each token

updateAddress(address,address,address,ad.notice: Updates the addresses of the various components of the contract.

updateExerciseDelegate(address,bool).notice: Updates the exercise delegate for the caller's option.
